Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chicken Breast{260} and stir-fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim and cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80} into thirds.

Once the chicken has browned, stir in the onion and Tenderstem®.

Stir-fry until the veg has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

While the veg cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the veg has softened, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Teriyaki Sauce{150} into the pan along with the @Water for the Sauce{50}.

Lower the heat and simmer until the sauce is sticky, the broccoli is tender and the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While it simmers, halve the @Red Chilli{½}(halved lengthways, deseeded and thinly sliced).

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Stir in the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5}.

Add a splash of water if it needs loosening, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice and serve with the teriyaki chicken on top.

Sprinkle over the chilli (add less chilli if you'd prefer things milder) to finish. Enjoy!

> This Teriyaki Sesame Chicken Breast is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

> Due to quality issues with green beans, you'll instead receive Tenderstem® broccoli. As such, the recipe photos are slightly different to what your dish will look like. Don't worry, we've updated the instructions so it'll still be just as delicious!